      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Sports Words Valid in Scrabble — Game Terminology</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Sports terminology is a goldmine for Scrabble players. Words borrowed from golf, cricket, fencing, and rugby have entered everyday English — and the official Scrabble dictionary. The key rule to remember: generic sport terms are valid, but proper nouns like team names and athlete names are never allowed. Here are 18 athletic words that can transform your next game.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (KAYAK)</p></div>
